# Kevin Indig – Recent LinkedIn Posts Analysis

---

## Post 1

**Date:** 3 July 2026

**Topic:** Audience building is replacing search traffic as a growth strategy

### Summary
Kevin argues that as search-generated clicks continue to decline, marketers need to maximize the value of the traffic they still receive. Rather than relying solely on SEO, he emphasizes building a loyal audience that returns directly to the brand. His message suggests that audience ownership is becoming increasingly important as traditional search becomes a less reliable acquisition channel.

### Main Takeaway
As organic search traffic declines, sustainable growth depends on building a loyal audience instead of relying exclusively on search engines.

