## Post 3

**Date:** 2 July 2026

**Topic:** Why original research alone doesn't guarantee AI citations

### Summary
Kevin explains that publishing original research is no longer enough to earn visibility in AI-generated answers. He observes that AI systems often cite aggregator websites that present data more clearly instead of the original source. He highlights that structured presentation of information—particularly dates and numerical data—combined with strong domain authority significantly improves the likelihood of being cited by AI systems.

### Main Takeaway
Original research creates value only when it is structured for AI extraction and supported by strong topical authority.

